            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Act 2: Second 1,500 Words",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The tension increases and the stakes continue to rise, as the Hero struggles to deal with the grief piling on them. At this point, minor surprises can keep the reader engaged and add to the mystery. These can take the form of misleading scenes, such as a door across the room suddenly closing. When the Sleuth opens the door, it leads to a closet. But why did the door close? Is there a secret passage in the closet?"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add more grief and stress to the Hero."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Show the Hero struggling to deal with the situation. "
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add another physical conflict – try to use a different form of physical conflict than before."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Include a surprise plot twist at the end of this section."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Is there suspense and a growing sense of menace?"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Build the plot so there is continuous action that proceeds logically."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 2 makes up the second 25% of the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Second 1,500 Words brings the story to the 50% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
